OL,3,CPrisons 'could collapse' as more than
OL,4,C2,500 prison staff could face
OL,5,Cdeportation
OL,7,F"We simply cannot afford to lose that
OL,8,Fmany frontline staff and if the
OL,9,Fgovernment does not exempt the prison
OL,10,Fservice from the new salary thresholds
OL,11,Fmany prisons will not be able to
OL,12,Ffunction and we will totally
OL,13,Fdestabilise the prison estate," Mr
OL,14,FFairhurst said.
OL,16,FThe Prison Governors' Association
OL,17,F(PGA) warned that the loss of these
OL,18,Fstaff would "leave a gap that cannot
OL,19,Feasily be filled" and that governors
OL,20,Fcannot run "safe stable prisons
OL,21,Fwithout the right number of officers".
